        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_azun" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>azun</orth><form type="participle"
                    ><orth>azt</orth></form></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>давать приют</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>give shelter</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>лелеять</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cherish</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ласкать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>caress</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>кормить</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>feed</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xæstæg næ xasta, sinxoni næ warzta, binonti næ azta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>родича не кормил, соседа не любил, домочадцев не ласкал</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>didn't feed the relative, didn't love the neighbor, didn't caress the
                                household</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 110</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>xæstægi xasta, sinxoni azta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>родственника кормил, с соседом был ласков</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>fed a relative, was gentle to a neighbor</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 108</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>iwazæg Xucawi iwazæg æj, zæǧgæ, ma sæ baaztoncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>«гость — Божий гость», — сказали они и приютили их</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>ʽthe guest is a guest of Godʼ, they said and gave them shelter</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            46</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Мало распространенное.</note>
                <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">Uncommon.</note>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Корень %iaz-%i, восходя к %i*ag-%i, мог иметь закономерное
                    развитие: %i*аg%i + %is-%i → %i*axš-%i, что мы и усматриваем в <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>беречь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āštīh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āšti</w>
                        <gloss><q>мир</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>согласие</q></gloss></mentioned>, а также в и. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axston"/> (из %iaxs-don%i) ‘гнездо’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axsǵiag"/> ‘любимый’; вариант %iaz-%i, с другой стороны,
                    отложился в д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astʼonæ"/> (из %iaz-donæ%i)
                    ‘гнездо’. Формально %iaz-%i относится к %iaxs-%i, как %iaraz-%i [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arazyn"/>] к %iaræxs-%i [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_aræxsyn"/>], %iæmbærz-%i [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbærzyn"/>] к %iæmbæxs-%i (*%iæmbærxs-%i) [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>], <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*az-</w>
                        <gloss><q>гнать</q></gloss></mentioned> к <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxsæ"/> ‘плеть’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ā-haz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>хватать</q></gloss></mentioned> к <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axæssun"/> ‘ловить’. См. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axston"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axsǵiag"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The root %iaz-%i, going back to %i*ag-%i, could have a natural
                    development: %i*аg%i + %is-%i → %i*axš-%i, что мы и усматриваем в <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxš-</w>
                        <gloss><q>cherish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>āxšti-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āštīh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āšti</w>
                        <gloss><q>peace</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>consent</q></gloss></mentioned>, and also in Iron <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axston"/> (from %iaxs-don%i) ʽnest’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axsǵiag"/> ‘favourite’; the variant %iaz-%i, on the other
                    hand, developed into Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_astʼonæ"/> (from
                    %iaz-donæ%i) ‘nest’. Formally, %iaz-%i relates to %iaxs-%i, like %iaraz-%i [<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>] to %iaræxs-%i [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_aræxsyn"/>], %iæmbærz-%i [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbærzyn"/>] to %iæmbæxs-%i (*%iæmbærxs-%i) [<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æmbæxsyn"/>], <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*az-</w>
                        <gloss><q>drive</q></gloss></mentioned> to <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_æxsæ"/> ‘lash’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*ā-haz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>grab</q></gloss></mentioned> to <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_axæssun"/> ‘catch’. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axston"
                    />, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_axsǵiag"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
